the structure of an animal or a plant

data.chText: 他身体的各个部位都清晰可见。
data.enText: Various parts of his anatomy were clearly visible.
an examination of what sth is like or why it happens

simple_means.memory_skill: ana 在旁边；类似 + tom 切割 + y 表行为 → 切开 → 解剖

example: he studied the anatomy of crimes

tr: alternative names for the body of a human being
example: the spirit is willing but the flesh is weak

tr: the branch of morphology that deals with the structure of animals

value.def: Anatomy is the study of the structure of the bodies of people or animals.
You can refer to your body as your anatomy.

example.ex: The ball hit him in the most sensitive part of his anatomy.
example.tran: 球击中了他身上最敏感的部位。

value.def: An animal's anatomy is the structure of its body.

example.ex: He had worked extensively on the anatomy of living animals.
example.tran: 他在活体解剖方面经验丰富。

value.def: The anatomy of a subject or an idea is an examination or investigation of it.

example.ex: This was a troubling essay on the anatomy of nationhood.
example.tran: 这是一篇剖析民族主义的让人不安的文章。
